sub_title: I'm an archaeologist by original intention and a computer scientist by final decision.
summary: I studied archaeology for my BA and MSc, but always focused on digital techniques and web technologies specifically. After my studies I pursued a career in web development, working on front- and backend as well as server maintenance and client liaison for 6 years. In 2022, I completed my PhD in Digital Archaeology at Leiden University, researching the use of text mining in archaeological grey literature, specifically the Malta reports archived by DANS and the RCE. I'm currently a postdoc in the EXALT project, further building on my PhD research.
